    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-03-07T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-03-07T18:00:00-05:00" n="346"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d346">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">810.79611 Pan American Airways, Inc./303:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Panama</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">South</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Panama</hi>
                        </placeName> [, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-03-07T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 7, 1929—6 p.m.</date>]<lb/>[Received 9:40 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>16. Your 14, February 28, 6 p.m. I am informed that article 25 of contract has
                    been revised to read: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“The stipulations of this are subject to the obligations which the
                            Republic of Panama has undertaken or may undertake with the United
                            States of America through treaties, conventions, agreements, or
                            regulations”.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>I assume that this covers commercial aviation as well as provisions concerning
                    radio in article 5.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">South</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
